[2
Yes, still here. I've been out of the office for the last three days.
Sorry for not getting back sooner.
I had three appointments this week. Monday and Tuesday at the internal
medicine physician and Thursday with the neurologist. Results from the
blood work on Monday revealed a drop in the white cell count and a normal
differential. I asked him for the exact levels but he continued to give me
the "within normal" response. He then told me that if my next blood test
proved to be normal, that there was very little he could do for me. So much
for him. I also saw the neurologist and passed all of his physical exams.
He said that the fasiculations could very well be stress related and that
there would be nothing he could do for me except put me on Klonopin. I
rejected this option until he could tell me that he had ruled out a
majority of the potential diagnosis that you had forwarded to me. He agreed
to give me an EMG, a review of all blood work to date and more blood work
if necessary after the EMG. If these items turned up negative, he would do
a spinal tap to rule out several other possibilities.
So that's where I stand. I will pursue the additional blood work and tests
that you suggested with the neurologist. If all tests are negative I will
then move on to a toxicologist, which someone you mentioned recommended.
Sorry, not much to report for the amount of time I spent at the doctors
offices this week. It seems like neither of these physicians really want to
diagnose this thing. My next appointment is Aug 24 for white cell blood
work and Sept 1 for the EMG (his earliest availability).
Thanks again for your concern and the wealth of information. I'll forward
as much as possible after the next appointments.
PS. I checked the http://www.nei.nih.gov/publications/histo.htm site you
mentioned in your last e-mail. The symptoms don't appear to be the same. My
vision is very good and I have not been seeing spots or patches. I just
seem to have twitches on the left side of my face which affect my left
eyelid at times. The site, however, is packed with useful info on many
other illnesses and they have a nice search facility.
