Date: Tue, 4 Aug 1998 09:27:43 -0400
From: Rob Shipman <rob@visgen.com>

I've been following the discussion and agree that histoplasmosis should be
tested for at the outset. The one website I would check with respect to the
involvement of the CNS and specifically the eyes would be the National Eye
Institute at the NIH <http://www.nei.nih.gov/publications/histo.htm>. This
site is deals with the issue of Ocular Histoplasmosis Syndrome which has a
number of similarities to the list of symptoms provided by the individual.
--
Rob Shipman PhD
Senior Scientist
Visible Genetics Inc.
Toronto, Ontario, Canada
e-mail: rob@visgen.com
